Here’s a short print block you can paste either inside the `<style>` section (after your main rules) or as a separate file linked with `media="print"`:

```html
/* ---------- PRINT STYLES ---------- */
@media print {

  /* Use light background and high contrast text */
  body {
    background: #ffffff;
    color: #000000;
    font-size: 11pt;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  /* Remove form controls that don’t translate to paper */
  #languageSelect, label[for="languageSelect"] {
    display: none;
  }

  /* Show all language blocks sequentially for reference */
  .hotline {
    display: block !important;
    background: none;
    border: 1pt solid #000;
    margin-bottom: 0.7cm;
    page-break-inside: avoid;
  }

  /* Keep links visible for offline readers */
  a[href]::after {
    content: " (" attr(href) ")";
    font-size: 9pt;
  }

  footer {
    background: none;
    border-top: 1pt solid #000;
    font-size: 9pt;
    font-style: italic;
    text-align: center;
    padding-top: 0.3cm;
  }

  /* Remove margins added by browsers */
  @page {
    margin: 1.5cm;
  }
}
```

**How it prints**

- Hides the language drop‑down but renders **every** hotline block so all supported languages appear on the PDF.  
- Adds the URL or phone number in parentheses after each link so it’s usable offline.  
- Keeps legibility and spacing consistent; no color ink required for readability.  
- Prevents page breaks in the middle of each hotline block.

